transcript:
This is the iPhone 17 Pro Max in Cosmic Orange, and this is what I said about it in my full review.

Right, okay, let's open the box. Oh, it's everything I'd hoped for. Let's do the peel, here we go.
It feels like it's not titanium anymore. It's an aluminum unibody frame. If you're thinking between the orange and the other colors that you can choose from with the, with the Pro Max, or or the Pro, I think get it.
What I want to know immediately is, does it wobble on the surface of the table? No, not really. Seeing that again, that little thing at the top of the screen is actually a bit of a, quite nice.
Oh, hang on. I, I used to moan about Dynamic Island, didn't I? One thing I really want to try is the new selfie camera, and it's the first ever square sensor. This is the Apple that I love. They choose these features which will have a genuine benefit on the people using them.
I honestly think that this new selfie camera across the new iPhone lineup is possibly the biggest feature.
The ability just to press that button and do that. I've got no one here to do a group selfie with, because I have no friends. But Apple, I love you when you do these things, it's utterly lovely.

Okay, to save you some time, I've done some scouring of the reviews that have gone live about the iPhone 17 Pro and Pro Max. The actual frame itself is thicker and heavier, apparently, than the 16 Pro Max.
The telephoto lens, yes, we have an eight times optical zoom. The battery is apparently better than the 16 Pro Max. I would only recommend getting this, I think, if you are a pro, or if you're just someone who wants the best of the best. In which case, you don't need me to tell you that, you'll just buy.
What I want now from you guys is to get involved down below. Have you bought this? What are you going to do with it? Why have you bought it? Have you not bought it? Have you gone for a completely different version of the new iPhone? See you down below. Cheers.

caption: Initial impressions, DM if you guys have specific questions!
transcript: So, a lot of you guys have been asking me about my initial impressions of the new iPhone 17 Pro Max. I have to say that I actually really like this phone. Coming from the 15 Pro Max, it's not like a huge upgrade, but there are some noticeable differences. And the first one I would say is the battery life. Like this one, I think it's because this phone is brand new, and it hasn't really accustomed to my usage yet, but the battery, I've been using it all day, and I'm at 48%. So that's a plus. Also, the screen is a little bit bigger than it used to be, uh, compared to the 15. The camera is much better, especially with the zoom. I also love the color. I mean, I wanted something different. I had the gray iPhone before, now I have this cosmic orange. And I typically go for the colors that are like pretty vibrant and light. I did want to do silver, but honestly, I wanted something different because I already had gray, and that's kind of similar. A lot of the features that I like about this phone are actually because of the iOS update, like the new call holding feature, the call screening features, like the liquid glass situation. I like the way that the icons look. Ignore my notifications. I know I have too many, I know I have to clear them, but we're just not going to talk about that. This extra button here, I know that this was available on the 16, I didn't have the 16, but, um, you know, it's pretty neat, but I don't feel like I'm going to use it that much. Honestly, it's not like that big of an upgrade. Like, I would say that if you have, the 13, which my brother had, even he was like, "Oh, you know, it's a really nice phone, but it doesn't feel that much different." So, I feel like, is it worth it? Mm, probably not. It really depends on the state of your phone, and how you use it. If you are a user that uses the camera a lot, then yeah. Because this camera is out of control. Now, regarding the price of the phone, it did stay the same to the 16, 16 Pro Max, I should say, and there are a lot of carrier deals. If you're willing to stay with your carrier for two years, I would say you should definitely upgrade, because a lot of the deals that are out there, are through trade-in credits. So, essentially, it makes the overall price of the phone cheaper. So, in my case, I have T-Mobile, and they gave us $830 uh, per line, we had to trade in the device. It really didn't make sense to keep my 15 Pro Max, especially if I was having issues with it. Those are my initial thoughts about the iPhone 17 Pro Max.

Apple‚Äôs iPhone 17 Pro Max in the highly sought-after cosmic orange color has experienced a tremendous surge in demand, selling out within just three days after pre-bookings opened for in-store pickup at Apple stores in both the US and India. According to company staff, the cosmic orange variant of the iPhone 17 Pro Max is currently out of stock across all storage options due to overwhelming pre-orders. In India, the entire iPhone Pro Max series is not available for pre-order with an in-store pickup option, and the cosmic orange color is not available for pre-order for either the Pro Max or Pro series for pickup at stores. Apple specialists apologized for the inconvenience and indicated efforts are underway to restock the popular color as soon as possible.
